public class ErrorEvent
extends com.google.gwt.event.shared.GwtEvent<ErrorEvent.Handler>

Event to notify that one or more visualization errors have occurred on the visualization, or have been cleared from it.

This event is supported only by Rhizosphere instances. If you are accessing Rhizosphere as a Google Visualization via GVizRhizosphere you should then rely on ErrorHandler.ErrorEvent.

Author:
battlehorse@google.com (Riccardo Govoni)

Fires an ErrorEvent on all registered handlers in the handler source.

Parameters:
source - the source of the handlers
cleared - Whether the errors have been cleared from the visualization or a new one is being added.
